FuncDef:
The acl ipv4-multicast-fib-miss enable command enables IPv4 MFIB-MISS packets to match against ACLs in the blacklist, whitelist, or user-defined flow.
The undo acl ipv4-multicast-fib-miss enable command disables IPv4 MFIB-MISS packets from matching against ACLs in the blacklist, whitelist, or user-defined flow.
By default, IPv4 MFIB-MISS packets are disabled from matching against ACLs in the blacklist, whitelist, or user-defined flow.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To enable IPv4 MFIB-MISS packets to match against ACLs in the blacklist, whitelist, or user-defined flow, run the acl ipv4-multicast-fib-miss enable command.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
